(1043, 5, 'Microsoft\'s Activision Blizzard takeover sparked by both companies failing to buy TikTok, Kotick says', 'https://www.eurogamer.net/microsofts-activision-blizzard-takeover-sparked-by-both-companies-failing-to-buy-tiktok-kotick-says', '<img src=\"https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Untitled-1_62oDWFG.jpg?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp\" /> <p>\nFormer Activision Blizzard boss <a data-keyword=\"true\" href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/personas/bobby-kotick\">Bobby Kotick</a> has shared the conversation he had with Microsoft boss Satya Nadella that would later lead to <a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/microsoft-has-finally-bought-activision-blizzard\">Xbox buying the Call of Duty maker for $67.8bn</a>.\n</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/microsofts-activision-blizzard-takeover-sparked-by-both-companies-failing-to-buy-tiktok-kotick-says\">Read more</a></p>', '', '2025-02-12 18:34:47'),
(1044, 5, 'PlayStation State of Play February 2025 - Ghost of Yotei and Death Stranding 2?', 'https://www.eurogamer.net/playstation-state-of-play-live-report-february-2025-ghost-of-yotei-and-death-stranding-2', '<img src=\"https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Untitled-1_t5VLGrW.jpg?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp\" /> <p>What is the state of play? Well, tonight Sony is going to tell us in a PlayStation State of Play broadcast, which begins at a not horrendous time of 10pm UK (5pm ET / 11pm CET). As always, we\'ll be running a blow-by-blow report here in this article, where you can also watch the stream and chat to us.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/playstation-state-of-play-live-report-february-2025-ghost-of-yotei-and-death-stranding-2\">Read more</a></p>', 'Blockbuster, PS5, Third person, Action Adventure, Ghost of Yōtei, Single Player, Kojima Productions, Shooter, Death Stranding 2', '2025-02-12 18:23:01'),
(1045, 5, 'Bobby Kotick says Activision Blizzard harassment lawsuits were \"fake\" and simply a \"plan\" to drive up union membership', 'https://www.eurogamer.net/bobby-kotick-says-activision-blizzard-fake-lawsuits-were-simply-a-union-plan-to-drive-up-membership', '<img src=\"https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Untitled-1_wV9zLHw.jpg?width=1920&height=1920&fit=bounds&quality=80&format=jpg&auto=webp\" /> <p>\nEx-Activision Blizzard boss <a data-keyword=\"true\" href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/personas/bobby-kotick\">Bobby Kotick</a> has described the legal action taken by multiple government agencies over alleged harrassment at his former company as \"fake lawsuits\", which he says were deliberately planned by a union in a bid to increase its membership.\n</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.eurogamer.net/bobby-kotick-says-activision-blizzard-fake-lawsuits-were-simply-a-union-plan-to-drive-up-membership\">Read more</a></p>', 'Activision Blizzard', '2025-02-12 17:50:59'),
